        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>As you are now so little on your Farm, you may not be aware that the necks of your horses are badly galled, as I have been informed by two persons.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I hope you will immediately attend to this, for though I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be very sorry to give trouble or annoyance to yourself from whom I have always received much civility, I must for the sake of humanity attend to this.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> A conviction for working Horses with galled necks is easily obtainable, on sufficient evidence being produced &amp; I was most unwillingly compelled, after vainly remonstrating with M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ainslie by letter on the subject, to get the Officer of the Royal Humane Soc. to come down here &amp; attend to the case, &amp; M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ainslie was fined by the Magistrates at the Bromley Session.—<ref target="#foot.f5"/> I sincerely hope that you will at once make enquiries &amp; give strict orders to your Bailiff not to work any horse with a wounded neck<ref target="#foot.f6"/>—</p>
<p>&amp; | I remain | Dear Sir | Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
